@page "/whoami"


<div class="container-fluid top-margin-medium bottom-margin-large">

    <h2 class="white-text text-center mb-5 vp-anim-3">Who Am I?</h2>

    <div class="container vp-anim-5">
        <p class="main-color text-center">
            My career started as an <span class="stand-out-text">Industrial Engineer</span>: 
            managing factory logistics and automating order processes.
            It was a challenging and interesting job, yet it didn’t have the aspect of software development that I most enjoy:
            <span class="stand-out-text">design and creation</span>.
        </p>

        <p class="main-color text-center">
            So, to fulfill that need to create, I started focusing myself on programming and developing the projects
            that I wanted to see come to life.
        </p>

        <p class="main-color text-center">
            My current goal is, not only to become a <span class="stand-out-text">world-class programmer</span>,
            but also to <span class="stand-out-text">share</span> the <span class="stand-out-text">knowledge</span> I acquire,
            with everyone that also has a passion for coding.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="empty-block"></div>

<div class="container-fluid main-color text-center vp-anim-4">
    <h2>So, what kind of projects do I work on?</h2>
</div>


<div class="container-fluid top-margin-medium">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-5">
            <div class="card text-center main-background-color">
                <i class="fas fa-ghost image-spacing white-text scale-up vp-anim-3" style="font-size: 10em"></i>
                <div class="card-body vp-anim-4">
                    <h3 class="card-title white-text mb-4">Video Games/Simulations</h3>
                    <p class="main-color">
                        Be it a simple <span class="stand-out-text">2D platformer</span>, 
                        an <span class="stand-out-text">action-packed 3D Shooter</span>,
                        or a <span class="stand-out-text">real-time fluid simulation</span> 
                        I love working on my own worlds.
                    </p>
                    <p class="main-color">
                        There is no joy like creating something tangible from nothing, 
                        and video games/simulations are the best way to do so.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
            <div class="card text-center main-background-color">
                <i class="fas fa-globe image-spacing white-text scale-up vp-anim-3" style="font-size: 10em"></i>
                <div class="card-body vp-anim-4">
                    <h3 class="card-title white-text mb-4">Web Development</h3>
                    <p class="main-color">Web applications allow us to do <span class="stand-out-text">anything</span>, 
                    <span class="stand-out-text">everywhere</span>.
                        I love working with <span class="stand-out-text">ASP.NET</span>, and build different types of projects.
                    </p>
                    <p class="main-color">
                        Its versatility allows to create solutions that range from a 
                        <span class="stand-out-text">portfolio website</span> like this one,
                        to other project types, like, <span class="stand-out-text">browser games</span>
                        and <span class="stand-out-text">web apps</span>.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-5">
            <div class="card text-center main-background-color">
                <i class="fas fa-file-excel image-spacing white-text scale-up vp-anim-3" style="font-size: 10em"></i>
                <div class="card-body vp-anim-4">
                    <h3 class="card-title white-text mb-4">MS Office Automation</h3>
                    <p class="main-color mb-0">
                        MS Office is everyone's enemy, right?
                    </p>
                    <p class="main-color">
                        It <span class="stand-out-text">doesn't need to be</span>.
                    </p>
                    <p class="main-color">
                        With <span class="stand-out-text">VBA automation</span> and 
                        <span class="stand-out-text">User Forms</span>,
                        I automate repetitive tasks so that everyone can <span class="stand-out-text">focus on big picture</span> problems.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

